{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783944645363,"sessionID":"ses_0a4a439a4ffe52Yfhj76CZK3oI","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_00_8dkrrnAN7h2xOV5p2JSQ4479","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"{\n  \"openQuestions\": [\n    {\"id\": \"q-residual-1\", \"text\": \"Should v1.5 add optional pixel-comparison mode for PDFs, or is text-extraction-only acceptable?\", \"priority\": \"P2\", \"source\": \"iteration-010.md\"},\n    {\"id\": \"q-residual-2\", \"text\": \"Can one canonical representation cover DOCX and HTML without creating false equivalence?\", \"priority\": \"P1\", \"source\": \"iteration-010.md\"},\n    {\"id\": \"q-residual-3\", \"text\": \"Should snapshots be encrypted at rest?\", \"priority\": \"P2\", \"source\": \"iteration-010.md\"},\n    {\"id\": \"q-residual-4\", \"text\": \"Should there be a zero-JS fallback for the HTML report?\", \"priority\": \"P1\", \"source\": \"iteration-010.md\"},\n    {\"id\": \"q-residual-5\", \"text\": \"Should v2.0 support cross-format comparison (e.g., DOCX vs Markdown)?\", \"priority\": \"P2\", \"source\": \"iteration-010.md\"}\n  ],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n    {\"id\": \"q1\", \"text\": \"Which canonical representation and extraction pipeline best preserve semantic structure?\", \"resolvedBy\": \"iteration-002.md\", \"resolution\": \"Markdown/mdast as canonical hub; unified.js ecosystem for multi-format AST pipeline; two-pass extraction + normalization model; format capability tiers defined.\"},\n    {\"id\": \"q2\", \"text\": \"Which diff algorithm strategy best combines readable changes, structural awareness, and noise suppression?\", \"resolvedBy\": \"iteration-003.md\", \"resolution\": \"AST-aware structural diff (Dijkstra-based, inspired by difftastic) with word-level text fallback for leaf nodes; Myers word-diff for unsupported formats.\"},\n    {\"id\": \"q3\", \"text\": \"Which automatic snapshot lifecycle is safe, atomic, recoverable?\", \"resolvedBy\": \"iteration-004.md\", \"resolution\": \"Explicit command capture; hash-of-path identity; SHA-256 content hashing; atomic write via temp+rename; configurable retention (default: last 10 per file, 30-day TTL); explicit-pair fallback.\"},\n    {\"id\": \"q4\", \"text\": \"Which local HTML report architecture is accessible, secure, self-contained?\", \"resolvedBy\": \"iteration-005.md\", \"resolution\": \"Self-contained single .html file; CSP meta tag; dual view modes (inline + side-by-side); fidelity warning system; WCAG 2.1 AA accessibility; zero external dependencies.\"},\n    {\"id\": \"q5\", \"text\": \"Which runtime, portable interface, dependency set, and standalone-skill workflow best suit v1?\", \"resolvedBy\": \"iteration-006.md\", \"resolution\": \"Node.js/TypeScript; unified/remark/rehype ecosystem; npm package with public API; CLI for direct use; OpenCode skill wrapper for AI workflow integration.\"},\n    {\"id\": \"q6\", \"text\": \"What existing libraries and products exist for document diff/compare?\", \"resolvedBy\": \"iteration-001.md\", \"resolution\": \"difftastic (structural diff, 25.6k stars), delta (diff renderer, 31.4k), diff-match-patch (text diff, archived), diff-so-fancy (renderer, 18.1k). No existing tool fills the standalone document diff niche.\"},\n    {\"id\": \"q7\", \"text\": \"What security constraints apply to untrusted document input?\", \"resolvedBy\": \"iteration-007.md\", \"resolution\": \"4-layer defense: input validation, parser hardening, output sanitization, resource limits. DOMPurify for HTML, XML bomb protection for DOCX, CSP for report output.\"},\n    {\"id\": \"q8\", \"text\": \"What fixture corpus and measurable acceptance criteria should gate v1?\", \"resolvedBy\": \"iteration-009.md\", \"resolution\": \"~30 fixture pairs across 6 categories; 11 measurable acceptance criteria; 10 performance benchmarks; 5 manual review cases; automated quality gate pipeline.\"}\n  ],\n  \"keyFindings\": [\n    {\"finding\": \"Node.js/TypeScript with unified.js ecosystem is the recommended v1 runtime\", \"iteration\": 6, \"confidence\": \"high\"},\n    {\"finding\": \"Markdown/mdast is the recommended canonical intermediate format\", \"iteration\": 2, \"confidence\": \"high\"},\n    {\"finding\": \"AST-aware structural diff with word-level text fallback is the recommended diff strategy\", \"iteration\": 3, \"confidence\": \"high\"},\n    {\"finding\": \"Self-contained HTML report with CSP, fidelity warnings, and dual-view modes\", \"iteration\": 5, \"confidence\": \"high\"},\n    {\"finding\": \"Explicit-command snapshot lifecycle with atomic writes and configurable retention\", \"iteration\": 4, \"confidence\": \"high\"},\n    {\"finding\": \"4-layer defense-in-depth security model for untrusted documents\", \"iteration\": 7, \"confidence\": \"high\"},\n    {\"finding\": \"CLI Library with HTML Output (Shape C) selected over Browser SPA and Desktop App\", \"iteration\": 8, \"confidence\": \"high\"},\n    {\"finding\": \"~30 fixture pairs, 11 acceptance criteria, 10 performance benchmarks for v1 validation\", \"iteration\": 9, \"confidence\": \"medium\"},\n    {\"finding\": \"10-phase decomposition for implementation phases 002-010\", \"iteration\": 10, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}\n  ],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n    {\"approach\": \"Automerge-style CRDT merging\", \"reason\": \"Solves distributed merging, not local comparison\", \"iteration\": 1},\n    {\"approach\": \"Direct format-to-format comparison\", \"reason\": \"N×M adapter combinatorial explosion\", \"iteration\": 2},\n    {\"approach\": \"Pure line-based diff for structured docs\", \"reason\": \"Misses structural changes, reflow false positives\", \"iteration\": 3},\n    {\"approach\": \"Browser-first SPA\", \"reason\": \"Cannot support snapshot lifecycle or CLI integration\", \"iteration\": 8},\n    {\"approach\": \"Electron/Tauri desktop app\", \"reason\": \"Excessive dependency weight for CLI-first use case\", \"iteration\": 8},\n    {\"approach\": \"Python-only implementation\", \"reason\": \"Lacks unified.js AST ecosystem\", \"iteration\": 8},\n    {\"approach\": \"Git-dependent workflow\", \"reason\": \"Violates core requirement of working without Git\", \"iteration\": 8}\n  ],\n  \"rejectedPatterns\": [],\n  \"promotedIdeas\": [],\n  \"blockedStopHistory\": []\n}","filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/136-standalone-document-diff-skill/001-research-and-requirements/research/lineages/document-diff-2/findings-registry.json"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/136-standalone-document-diff-skill/001-research-and-requirements/research/lineages/document-diff-2/findings-registry.json","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/136-standalone-document-diff-skill/001-research-and-requirements/research/lineages/document-diff-2/findings-registry.json","time":{"start":1783944645354,"end":1783944645362}},"id":"prt_f5b62cc13001qZ0GpaqPW5fO98","sessionID":"ses_0a4a439a4ffe52Yfhj76CZK3oI","messageID":"msg_f5b62bec9001xNp4YhTJ1orX1Z"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783944652744,"sessionID":"ses_0a4a439a4ffe52Yfhj76CZK3oI","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_01_fYXsQM30YjVnc5Wwx0TD1449","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Deep Research Dashboard\n\n## Iteration Table\n\n| Run | Focus | newInfoRatio | Findings | Status |\n|-----|-------|-------------|----------|--------|\n| 1 | Broad survey of existing document diff ecosystem | 0.9 | 6 | complete |\n| 2 | Canonical representation and extraction pipelines | 0.8 | 6 | complete |\n| 3 | Diff algorithm comparison | 0.7 | 5 | complete |\n| 4 | Snapshot lifecycle design | 0.7 | 6 | complete |\n| 5 | HTML report architecture and security | 0.8 | 6 | complete |\n| 6 | Runtime selection and dependency analysis | 0.7 | 5 | complete |\n| 7 | Security constraints for untrusted documents | 0.8 | 6 | complete |\n| 8 | Architecture shape comparison | 0.6 | 5 | complete |\n| 9 | Fixture corpus and acceptance criteria | 0.6 | 5 | complete |\n| 10 | Integration synthesis and later-phase recommendations | 0.4 | 6 | complete |\n\n## Question Status\n\n| Question | Status | Resolved In |\n|----------|--------|-------------|\n| Q1: Canonical representation pipeline | **Answered** | Iteration 2 |\n| Q2: Diff algorithm strategy | **Answered** | Iteration 3 |\n| Q3: Snapshot lifecycle | **Answered** | Iteration 4 |\n| Q4: HTML report architecture | **Answered** | Iteration 5 |\n| Q5: Runtime, interface, skill workflow | **Answered** | Iteration 6 |\n| Q6: Existing libraries and products | **Answered** | Iteration 1 |\n| Q7: Security constraints | **Answered** | Iteration 7 |\n| Q8: Fixture corpus and acceptance criteria | **Answered** | Iteration 9 |\n\n**Answered: 7/8** (Q8 partially — targets are estimated, need real measurement)\n\n## Convergence Trend\n\nnewInfoRatio trend: [0.9 0.8 0.7 0.7 0.8 0.7 0.8 0.6 0.6 0.4] — clearly trending down as expected\n\nComposite stop score: Not calculated (convergenceThreshold=0, stopPolicy=max-iterations)\n\n## Dead Ends\n\n| Approach | Why | Iteration |\n|----------|-----|-----------|\n| CRDT merging as diff foundation | Distributed merging, not local comparison | 1 |\n| Direct format-to-format comparison | N×M adapter explosion | 2 |\n| Pure line-based diff for docs | Misses structural changes | 3 |\n| Browser-first SPA | No snapshot lifecycle or CLI | 8 |\n| Electron/Tauri desktop app | Excessive dependency weight | 8 |\n| Python-only implementation | No unified.js ecosystem | 8 |\n| Git-dependent workflow | Violates core requirement | 8 |\n\n## Blocked Stops\n\nNone (convergenceThreshold=0 with max-iterations stop policy)\n\n## Next Focus\n\nSynthesis phase — compile all iteration findings into canonical research/research.md.\n","filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/136-standalone-document-diff-skill/001-research-and-requirements/research/lineages/document-diff-2/deep-research-dashboard.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/136-standalone-document-diff-skill/001-research-and-requirements/research/lineages/document-diff-2/deep-research-dashboard.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/136-standalone-document-diff-skill/001-research-and-requirements/research/lineages/document-diff-2/deep-research-dashboard.md","time":{"start":1783944652732,"end":1783944652743}},"id":"prt_f5b630b3a001lkVaL5OI26rAow","sessionID":"ses_0a4a439a4ffe52Yfhj76CZK3oI","messageID":"msg_f5b62bec9001xNp4YhTJ1orX1Z"}}
